article.headline: UC Davis 45, Winston-Salem 14
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Greg Denham completed 13 of 16 passes for 220 yards and three touchdowns in UC Davis' 45-14 victory over winless Winston-Salem State on Saturday night. Chris Carter caught five passes for 91 yards and one touchdown and Dean Rogers also caught a TD pass for the Aggies (3-3). Jarrett Dunston was 11 of 19 for 152 yards and two TDs and receiver Lerenzo Barr caught a 31-yard touchdown pass in the third quarter for the Rams (0-6). Six different UC Davis players scored a touchdown, including Joseph Gray who returned a kickoff 81 yards in the third quarter. Denham tossed two touchdown passes in the first quarter and another in second as the Aggies rolled to a 38-0 halftime lead. The Rams lost three fumbles in the first half, including a mishandled handoff that was recovered and returned 34 yards for a score by Eric Sobotka.
